    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-01T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-01T03:00:00-05:00" n="1026"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1026">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.5493/12–149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Second Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bacon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-01T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 1, 1949—4 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:40 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2520. Embtel 2482, November 26.<note n="18" xml:id="d1026fn18">Not
                        printed.</note> Bacon and Clough attended hearing re Labor Union after
                    receiving phone call from Aliens Affairs Office stating Union desired appearance
                    Soule and Bacon. Soule’s absence not commented on nor name mentioned at hearing.
                    Employees’ demand for separation allowance reduced to 2 months but maintenance
                    and other demands renewed plus demand that all payments based on wage scale be
                    recalculated according to rise cost of living. At conclusion Union official
                    stated case transferred to Labor Bureau which would begin preliminary
                    investigation possibly December 3.</p>
                <p>Inform Peiping.</p>
                <p>Pass Army.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bacon</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
